# No Mocking Supabase in Tests

**NEVER mock Supabase clients or auth functions in tests.** All tests must use real Supabase calls against the cloud project.

## Banned Patterns

```typescript
// ❌ All of these are banned
vi.mock('@/lib/supabase.client')
vi.mock('@/lib/supabase.server')
vi.mock('@/lib/supabase.client', () => ({ sbc: { auth: { signUp: vi.fn() } } }))
vi.mock('@/context/auth-provider')
const mockGetUser = vi.fn()
```

## Use Instead

- **Test users:** Create with `supabaseServer.auth.admin.createUser({ email, password, email_confirm: true })`
- **Sign in:** Use real `sbc.auth.signInWithPassword()` calls
- **Token validation:** Use real access tokens from sign-in sessions
- **Cleanup:** Delete test users with `supabaseServer.auth.admin.deleteUser(userId)` in `afterAll`
- **Test emails:** Use disposable format `test-{uuid}@sermonize-test.com`

## Why

Mocking Supabase hides real integration failures. Tests should verify the actual auth plumbing works end-to-end — token issuance, validation, expiry, and rejection.
